{"title":"Updated Surly Big Easy 2.0 eCargo Bike Gets More Comfortable & Better at Hauling","link":"https://bikerumor.com/surly-big-easy-2-0-e-cargo-bike/","date":1711643725000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-hero-800x533.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" alt=\"(Photos/Surly Bikes)\" /></p>\n<p>Minnesota’s <a href=\"https://surlybikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Surly Bikes</a> has always championed the ethos that we should ride bikes and bring stuff as much as possible. And, they’re making it as easy as possible to do so with the release of the newly updated longtail electric cargo bike, the <a href=\"https://surlybikes.com/bikes/big_easy\" target=\"_blank\">Big</a> Easy. The Big Easy has been around for a while, and it’s paid its dues. But now it’s better. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Surly Updated Big Easy haulin' precious cargo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-haulin-precious-cargo.jpg 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Surly Bikes)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Big Easy, in addition to the rest of their line of <em>Bikes that Haul</em>, shows you that Surly is serious about ditching the car and haulin’ with your bike. You can choose how you want to haul your goods with the analog longtail cargo bike, the <a href=\"https://surlybikes.com/bikes/big_dummy\" target=\"_blank\">Big Dummy</a>, or the more compact electric cargo bike, the <a href=\"https://surlybikes.com/bikes/skid_loader\" target=\"_blank\">Skid Loader</a>. Surly is making it easy, as all of these bikes are fairly affordable.  </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Big Easy 2.0</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Surly Updated Big Easy toolin'\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-toolin.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The updated Big Easy, a bike that Surly calls the “18-wheeler of the cargo world, minus the diesel fumes”. starts with updated frame geometry. Adding stiffness, and expanding rider fitment makes for better riding and a more comfy Big Easy. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Surly Updated Big Easy ATB with ladder\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-ATB-with-ladder.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Surly has also added double-seated capacity – including adaptor-free child seat compatibility. The Big Easy “rides and feels like a normal-length bike, ” and the upright, engaged rider position keeps things comfortable. The new thru-axles help keep things stiff while under loads.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The entire component group that Surly has chosen for the Big Easy was selected for the demands of hauling heavy cargo. For instance, the Tektro four-piston, hydraulic brakes bring all of the stopping power. Also, expanding rider fit per size by adding a long-throw dropper post to improve bike sharing among different-sized riders. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Big Easy Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Surly Updated Big Easy new motor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-new-motor.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Surly Updated Big Easy Bosch display\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Surly-Updated-Big-Easy-Bosch-display.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Equipped with the most powerful Bosch Cargo electric bike motor for elevated performance</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Features Surly dual-leg kickstand for unmatched stability when loading and unloading cargo<br />Two-seat compatibility for human passengers big or small – no adapter needed (Thule Yepp Nexxt Maxi and Burley Dash)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lower stand-over height for improved stability when stopping, mounting, and dismounting</li>\n\n\n\n<li>High-rise Surly Sunrise handlebars give riders leverage to control heavy loads and the body position to keep you comfortable </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Featuring updated Big Dummy bags with simplified design and consistent cargo capacity</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Damping headset for smooth and stable handling under heavy loads</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Capable of running dual batteries for extended range</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Large-volume 26 